greenmirror.client

Interface TraceSelector

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FileTraceSelector

    public interface TraceSelector
    The interface that defines how trace selectors should be structured.

    Traces should be selected and retrieved in prepare(), not in getTrace(). getTrace() is only meant to be the simple getter.

    Author:
    Karim El Assal

      • prepare

        void prepare()
      throws TraceSelector.PreparationException
        Do some preparing, like retrieving the trace from a file or other class. This method should only be called once. This method might be renamed in the future to something like selectTrace() or retrieveTrace().
        Throws:
        TraceSelector.PreparationException - if something goes wrong during the preparation
